An employee died in a fall-of-ground incident at Harmony Gold’s Tshepong mine, near Welkom, on Thursday. An investigation into the accident is currently under way. “We are deeply saddened by the loss of our colleague at Tshepong. “Harmony’s management expresses their sincere condolences to our colleague’s family, friends and colleagues,” Harmony CEO Peter Steenkamp said in a statement issued on Friday.